			<div class="content" id="post-content-1704115">
									

<blockquote>
<p>Clearly setting up something big (i.e. the part of this cannon after the contest ends)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yup, we have a lot of material. We also wanted to set up a framework for people (who aren't the four of us) to write in after the contest voting period ends and all the canons open up.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>but Ganymede doesn't seem all that significant.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Google &quot;Ganymede&quot; and you might get some hints. (THAT part is just us &amp; our planning, not the framework for others to write in.)</p>
<p>In the story, though, a large part of the significance is, well, what the Ganymede Protocol <em>is</em>, and the effects that will have on the Foundation.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>And do even you know why Lament is doing all this?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Yup. :D</p>

